Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 80, 15. Name Kleonymos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0162.27.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1695)
